<emphasis id="46DE290FFFEAFF8AEF8A46A6FEAFFA15" box="[145,380,1473,1502]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Nothing known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CB0A696FFEAFF8AEF88468FFC57F9E6" pageId="8" pageNumber="215" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="7415F51DFFEAFF8AEF88468FFC57F9E6" blockId="8.[145,1348,1115,1935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="46DE290FFFEAFF8AEF88468FFC9DF9CE" box="[147,846,1512,1541]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Said to build a round nest of green material in trees, at least two meters from the ground.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CB0A696FFEAFF8AEF884554FDD4F99F" box="[147,519,1587,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215" type="breeding">
<paragraph id="7415F51DFFEAFF8AEF884554FDD4F99F" blockId="8.[145,1348,1115,1935]" box="[147,519,1587,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="46DE290FFFEAFF8AEF884554FECAF99F" box="[147,281,1587,1620]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">Breeding.</emphasis>
Nothing known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3CB0A696FFEAFF8AEF884539FD55F88B" pageId="8" pageNumber="215" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="7415F51DFFEAFF8AEF884539FD55F88B" blockId="8.[145,1348,1115,1935]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="46DE290FFFEAFF8AEF884539FE24F9B0" box="[147,503,1630,1659]" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Known only from a dozen museum specimens; the most recent records are two skins collected in 1988 from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="0CBDB58DFFEAFF8AEECA45D6FDE4F901" box="[465,567,1713,1738]" name="Liberia" pageId="8" pageNumber="215">Liberia</collectingCountry>
. Major threats to this species are not known, but it is probably being affected by ongoing habitat loss in the upper Guinean forests. This is a priority species for survey work in order to determine its current range and population status, and to investigate its ecology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
